Vice President Biden released a statement expressing his condolences on the death of former Israeli President Shimon Peres. He described Peres as a man of wisdom and eloquence, whose words stayed with you even after he left the room. Biden had the privilege of knowing Peres for 40 years and admired his compassion, energy, and curiosity. Peres was part of the generation that founded the Jewish State of Israel and dedicated his life to its service. He held every office, earned numerous awards and honors, and never stopped serving. Peres worked tirelessly to make Israel strong and secure, while also advocating for peace. Biden emphasized that Peres was the soul of Israel and his loss is felt not only in Israel but around the world. He extended his condolences to the people of Israel and Peres' family.